# Google API Agent Rules

## Screenshot Data Format

Screenshots flow through multiple pipelines. ALWAYS handle all three formats:

```python
if isinstance(data, dict):
    img_data = data.get("data", "")
elif isinstance(data, str):
    img_data = data  # raw base64
elif isinstance(data, bytes):
    img_data = base64.b64encode(data).decode()
```

## Image Data at Boundaries

- Gemini `inline_data.data` → bytes
- Veo `types.Image(image_bytes=...)` → needs bytes
- HTML `<img src="data:...;base64,...">` → needs base64 string
- JSON response → needs base64 string

Always convert at the boundary, never assume the format upstream.

## Model Names

| Model | Name |
|-------|------|
| Live translation | `gemini-2.5-flash-native-audio-latest` |
| Text generation | `gemini-2.5-flash` |
| Cheap text | `gemini-2.5-flash-lite` |
| Image generation | `gemini-2.5-flash-image` |
| Video generation | `veo-2.0-generate-001` |

## Veo Polling

Poll every 5s, max 300s. Wrap polling in try/except (network transients). Log elapsed time. If `operation.done` but no `generated_videos`, log the result object for debugging.

## Cost Budget

Total hackathon budget: $25. Memory video (~$2.50) is the most expensive single operation. Stylization is cheap (~$0.02/image). Always log costs via `log_api_call()`.
